  <!-- 
    KEY CONCEPT: ManufacturedItemDefinition vs AdministrableProductDefinition
    
    ManufacturedItemDefinition describes the PHYSICAL ITEM as it exists in the primary packaging, coming out of the manufacturing process. In this scenario, we have TWO manufactured items:
    1. A vial containing lyophilized powder (the active drug).
    2. An ampoule containing the diluent (solvent).
    
    AdministrableProductDefinition describes what the PATIENT ACTUALLY RECEIVES — 
    in this case, a single "Solution for injection" created after the powder is 
    reconstituted with the diluent. The AdministrableProductDefinition.producedFrom 
    element links back to BOTH of these ManufacturedItemDefinitions to show they 
    are used together to prepare it.
  -->

